<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09149e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09149e">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09149e"> 149(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> How many days to &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was <i>dies memorabilis</i> when last I struck the banks of this famous Luapula, the river Livingstone immortalised in his dying words, &ldquo;<mark>How many days to</mark> the Luapula?&rdquo; &hellip; Any place is tragically so many &ldquo;days&rdquo; off, and a day = fifteen miles&apos; journey. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 97</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
